6fair value measurements  sfas no.157 defines fair value as the price that would be received upon sale of an asset
or paid upon transfer of a liability in an orderly transaction between market participants at the measurement date and in the principal or most advantageous market for that asset or liability. the fair value should be calculated based on assumptions
that market participants would use in pricing the asset or liability, not on assumptions specific to the entity. in addition, the fair value of liabilities should include consideration of non-performance risk, including our own credit risk.
in addition to defining fair value, sfas no.157 expands the disclosure requirements around fair value and establishes a fair
value hierarchy for valuation inputs. the hierarchy prioritizes the inputs into three levels based on the extent to which inputs used in measuring fair value are observable in the market.each fair value measurement is
